@startuml
title eClaims.API - Architecture

actor Client
participant "eClaims.API\n(ASP.NET Core)" as API
participant "MongoDB / InMemory" as DB
participant "IRepository&lt;T&gt;\n(Repository / InMemoryRepository)" as Repo
participant "Configuration\n(MongoDbSettings)" as Config
participant "OpenAPI / Swagger" as Swagger
participant "Logging / DI" as DI

Client -> API: HTTP requests (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE)
activate API
API -> Swagger: Expose OpenAPI endpoints
API -> DI: Resolve IRepository&lt;Claim&gt; and settings
API -> Repo: Call GetAllAsync / GetByIdAsync / AddAsync / UpdateAsync / DeleteAsync
activate Repo
Repo -> DB: Read/Write collections (Claims)
activate DB
DB --> Repo: Data
deactivate DB
Repo --> API: Entities / Acknowledgement
deactivate Repo
API --> Client: HTTP responses (200/201/204)
deactivate API

note left of API
  - Controllers: ClaimsController, SeedController
  - Registered services: IRepository -> InMemoryRepository (or Repository when using MongoDB)
  - Settings loaded from MongoDbSettings section
end note

@enduml
